Description: Fragment of an uninscribed probably unfinished ring of a white and quite soft limestone. The upper surface contains a flat, plain and well-smoothed oval shape with traces of the tool used for smoothn it. The lower ring body is not preserved.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E13.2M, near floor
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 183)
